== Arepa Dough ==

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 375 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Drain polenta. In a #large bowl{}, crumble @precooked polenta{1%unit} into
small pieces, about the size of a pea. Add @tempura mix{82%g}, half the
@mozzarella cheese{1%cup}, and @olive oil{1%tbsp} to bowl with polenta.
Using your hands, mash to combine until tempura batter mix and mozzarella are
thoroughly incorporated, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Set dough aside to rest for ~{10%minutes}.

== Pickled Onion, Crema & Tomato ==

While dough rests, halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Quarter
@lime{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Dice @tomato{1} into 1/4-inch
pieces; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine onion, juice from half the lime,
@water{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cover tightly
with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until onion is softened and bright pink,
~{30%seconds}. Carefully remove plastic wrap and stir. Set aside to pickle,
stirring occasionally.

Place @sour cream{3%tbsp} in a separate small bowl. Add water 1 tsp at a time
until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper to
taste.

== Arepas ==

Divide dough into 8 equal portions (16 portions for 4 servings); shape each into
a ball. On a clean work surface, flatten each ball into a 1/4-inch-thick round
using the palm of your hand.

> If dough feels sticky, spray your work surface and hands with nonstick
> cooking spray.

Divide remaining mozzarella between tops of half the dough rounds. Top with
remaining dough rounds and press edges of dough rounds together to seal to form
arepas.

> Pinch and press edges while gently pressing down on tops of sealed arepas
> using the palm of your hand to ensure no cheese escapes while they cook!

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan
over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot, carefully add two arepas to pan. Cook
until bottoms begin to brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Carefully flip arepas. Cook until opposite sides begins to brown,
~{2-3%minutes}. Carefully transfer to a #baking sheet{}. Repeat with remaining
arepas.

> The oil will get hotter with each batch. If arepas begin to brown too
> quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Once all arepas are browned, bake on middle rack until dough is cooked through
and cheese has melted, ~{10-12%minutes}. Let pan cool slightly, then carefully
wipe out.

== Cantina Chicken ==

While arepas bake, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and
season all over with @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for arepas over medium-high heat. Add
chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide cheesy arepas between plates. Fan chicken next to arepas. Drizzle
everything with crema. Top with tomato, cilantro, and as much pickled onion as
you like (draining first). Squeeze remaining lime wedges over the top. Serve.